descript.abstract: GIS data set of main trail corridors in the State of California.
descript.purpose: Display of generalized and detailed regional trail routes. This can show existing and planned linkages between State, Federal, and local parks.

theme.themekt: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.0.1770
idinfo.accconst: REQUIRED: Restrictions and legal prerequisites for accessing the data set.
idinfo.useconst: REQUIRED: Restrictions and legal prerequisites for using the data set after access is granted.

attracc.attraccr: Accuracy of data varies depending on source data. For trails where the source data is a series of GPS points, the accuracy is high at the GPS point, but will lose accuracy between the points, since the trail is drawn in a straight line from GPS point to GPS point.

dataqual.complete: Trail completeness varies from trail to trail, as does the spatial precision. Many of the trails are obtain from other agencies, who provide the data in a variety of formats.

procstep.procdesc: Collected GIS data where available for main trails.
Digitized trail from hard copy and topographic maps for trails without GIS data available.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Length of feature in internal units.

attrdomv.udom: Positive real numbers that are automatically generated.

overview.eaover: Trail name, segment, precision, and source are documented.

cntorgp.cntper: REQUIRED: The person responsible for the metadata information.

metainfo.metstdn: FGDC Content Standards for Digital Geospatial Metadata
